<h2>Part 3: Efficient Account Appeal Process</h2>
<h3>3.1 Pre-Appeal Preparation</h3>
<p>Before submitting an appeal, complete the following preparations:</p>
<p><strong>1. Identify the root cause</strong></p>
<p>Log into Google Ads backend, go to <strong>"Optimization" → "Diagnostics"</strong> to view specific violation explanations. Carefully read the notification email from Google, which typically includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Specific ads or keywords in violation</li>
<li>Referenced policy clauses</li>
<li>Required corrective content</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. Gather evidence materials</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Screenshots and complete content of suspended ads</li>
<li>Landing page URLs and complete screenshots</li>
<li>Compliance qualification certificates for products/services</li>
<li>Business license, legal representative ID</li>
<li>Cooperation agreements with suppliers/brands (if brand authorization involved)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Develop correction plan</strong></p>
<p>Don't simply admit fault; <strong>demonstrate what changes you've already made</strong>:</p>
<ul>
